projects.description: Developed the Mixture Of Agents (MOA), a multi-layer inference system leveraging flexible input model sets from various API vendors, as an advanced iteration of projects like grog-moa and together-moa. MOA integrates multiple APIs, including OpenAI, Groq, DeepInfra, Together, Mistral, Nvidia, DeepSeek, Hugging Face, Anthropic, Google Gemini, Cohere, and Palm2, to aggregate and enhance AI model responses in real-time. Key features include an interactive chat interface, configurable model lists and layers, and real-time response streaming. Demonstrated a CLI showcasing the systemâ€™s ability to process and combine outputs from various models. Users can interact with the system through a user-friendly interface, which maintains conversational context and ensures seamless interactions. The project is highly configurable via YAML files, facilitating easy modifications. Licensed under Apache 2.0, the project acknowledges Groq and Together AI for their contributions. More details are available in my Medium article.
